results.name: Numbers n such that n! is the product of exactly two smaller factorials.
comment: x! is considered to be a trivial solution because (x!)! can be written as x!*(x!-1)!
All terms except 10 appear to be trivial solutions. Every factorial appears in this sequence.
reference: Richard K. Guy, Unsolved Problems in Number Theory, B23 Equal products of factorials, Springer, Third Edition, 2004, p. 123.
Laurent Habsieger (2019), Explicit bounds for the Diophantine equation A!B! = C!. Fibonacci Quarterly. 57, 1.
link: Laurent Habsieger, Explicit Bounds For The Diophantine Equation A!B! = C!, arXiv:1903.08370 [math.NT], 2019.
